🤖 🔹 PART 6: JENKINS SETUP (CLEAR)
✅ Install Jenkins
Install Jenkins
Open:
http://localhost:8080
✅ First Setup
Enter password
Install suggested plugins
Create user
✅ Install Plugins (IMPORTANT)

Go to:
👉 Manage Jenkins → Plugins

Install:

Git plugin
Pipeline
Docker Pipeline
✅ Create Pipeline Job
New Item
Name: conference-app
Select Pipeline
✅ Add Pipeline Code
pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {

        stage('Clone Code') {
            steps {
                git 'https://github.com/yourusername/conference-app.git'
            }
        }

        stage('Build Docker') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker build -t conference-app .'
            }
        }

        stage('Run App') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker run -d -p 8082:80 conference-app'
            }
        }
    }
}
✅ Run Jenkins
Save
Click Build Now
✅ Open App
http://localhost:8082
